    <div class="section">
        <h2><span class="icon">üöÄ</span> 2. Competition Strategy: The VoLT Framework</h2>
        <p>BAH competes by transitioning from general consulting to an **advanced technology integrator**, driven by the **Velocity, Leadership, and Technology (VoLT)** strategy.</p>

        <h3>Core Strategy: VoLT Breakdown</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><span class="key-point">Velocity:</span> Accelerating the deployment cycle of innovative solutions (e.g., AI integration).</li>
            <li><span class="key-point">Leadership:</span> Establishing market and intellectual leadership in critical tech domains.</li>
            <li><span class="key-point">Technology:</span> Prioritizing high-end engineering contracts over traditional advisory services.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Competitive Tactics</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>**Contracting Vehicles:** Utilizing long-established, trusted government contract mechanisms for streamlined access.</li>
            <li>**Acquisition:** Strategic use of Booz Allen Ventures for targeted acquisitions in niche, emerging tech (Quantum, Space).</li>
            <li>**Tech Focus:** Shifting delivery model to **cybersecurity, AI/ML, and 5G** solutions delivery.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2><span class="icon">üí°</span> 3. Core Differentiation & Barrier to Entry</h2>
        
        <table style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
            <tr>
                <th>Differentiating Factor</th>
                <th>Strategic Advantage</th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td><strong>High Security Clearances</strong></td>
                <td>A massive barrier to entry; allows BAH to access and execute the most sensitive, restricted contracts.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td><strong>Mission Specialization</strong></td>
                <td>Unlike generalist firms, 100+ years of focus on the unique demands and culture of the U.S. Federal Government.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
